name: Melanie - Agile Board
desc:
Use this board to get things done. It isn’t just about shipping a product, or checking off items on a list, or even about marking a project as Done. Getting things done is a process: it’s a way of thinking that involves planning, execution, iteration, and reflection.

Learn more here: https://blog.trello.com/how-to-scrum-and-trello-for-teams-at-work

data.text: Update from Byron:  I had the chance to discuss at some length the possibility of upgrading PyCSW to support ISO19115-3 with Angelos Tzotsos and Tom Kralidis, the primary contributors and maintainers of PyCSW and related libraries. I asked for some indiction of what would be involved and the email below is what was provided. I emphasised that there would be people in Aus/NZ who may want to provide the coding skills. Not sure that is what we got. Still in provides some idea of the scope of the work.

listing.name: Google Drive
listing.description:
The Google Drive Power-Up for Trello brings your files and folders to Trello cards. Search Google Drive right from Trello and attach relevant files and folders. See real-time previews and details and click back into Google Drive. It also lets you turn your Trello board into a Google Slides presentation with one click.

- Built in file search lets you attach folders and files from Google Drive to a Trello card on any version of Trello.
- See real-time information and previews for any Google Drive files or folders attached to cards.
- Turn your Trello board into a Google Slides presentation with one click.
